## 📂 3. Folder Structure Architecture
The project follows a **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** variation. Instead of organizing by file type (e.g., all components together, all hooks together), files are grouped by their **feature domain** inside `src/features`.

```text
c:\Workspace\Portfolio-forge\
├── next.config.ts         # Next.js build and routing config
├── package.json           # Project dependencies & scripts
├── tailwind.config.ts / postcss.config.mjs # Tailwind config
├── components.json        # Shadcn UI CLI configuration
├── middleware.ts          # Next.js Middleware (mainly for Clerk Auth)
└── src/                   # Main source code directory
    ├── app/               # Next.js App Router (Pages & Layouts)
    │   ├── (group)/       # Route groups (dashboard, explore, leaderboard)
    │   ├── sign-in/       # Clerk Sign-in Page
    │   ├── sign-up/       # Clerk Sign-up Page
    │   ├── layout.tsx     # Root layout (ClerkProvider, QueryProvider, Fonts)
    │   └── page.tsx       # Landing Page (Hero section)
    │
    ├── features/          # 🌟 Domain-specific logic (The core of the app)
    │   ├── api/           # API hooks/endpoints
    │   ├── auth/          # Authentication utilities
    │   ├── explore/       # Swipe Feed logic (components: PortfolioCard, RatingActions)
    │   ├── leaderboard/   # Leaderboard logic (components: LeaderboardTable)
    │   └── portfolio/     # User portfolio logic (components: PortfolioForm, StatsOverview)
    │
    ├── components/        # Shared/Global components
    │   └── ui/            # Shadcn & Aceternity UI components (Button, Card, Table, BackgroundBeams, etc.)
    │
    ├── lib/               # 3rd party library initializations (e.g., Prisma, Axios instances)
    ├── providers/         # Global React Context Providers (e.g., query-provider.tsx)
    ├── store/             # Global Zustand stores
    └── utils/             # Helper functions (e.g., cn() for Tailwind classes)
```

